(17, 'madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar Adventure Trips - Explore Unique Landscapes', 'Excursiones en Madagascar: Aventura y Naturaleza', 'Discover unforgettable Madagascar adventure trips!', 'Descubre emocionantes excursiones en Madagascar.', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'best travel, agence de voyage, explore travel, madagascar tourism, madagascar tours, madagascar trip, tour in madagascar, travel tours, private tour', 'img/uploads/images/img_6863d71401f328.28687522.webp', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', 'Madagascar', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(43, 43, 43); font-family: InterRegular; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">While Madagascar is an island in the Indian Ocean, it was originally settled by people of Indonesian and African descent, which you can clearly see when one looks at the inhabitants. Others have suggested that the people of Madagascar descended from Indonesians and Africans who mixed before their arrival on the isolated island, but studies prove people of Madagascar came from Borneo and Africa. It is not fully known how the inhabitants came there or if they were there already. Only later did Arabs, Indians and Jewish immigrants mix into the population of the island. The Malagasy way of thinking is a mixture of cultures, as well as their appearance and fashion style.</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(43, 43, 43); font-family: InterRegular; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify;\">While Madagascar is an island in the Indian Ocean, it was originally settled by people of Indonesian and African descent, which you can clearly see when one looks at the inhabitants. Others have suggested that the people of Madagascar descended from Indonesians and Africans who mixed before their arrival on the isolated island, but studies prove people of Madagascar came from Borneo and Africa. It is not fully known how the inhabitants came there or if they were there already. Only later did Arabs, Indians and Jewish immigrants mix into the population of the island. The Malagasy way of thinking is a mixture of cultures, as well as their appearance and fashion style.</span></p>', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
